item.title: sdwdate log: "please report this bug"
item.dc:creator: Patrick
item.description:
Above is real issue.

ak88:

Tor Bootstrap Result: ERROR (124).

Since it’s not persistent, not the root issue. Output is cosmetic only. Most likely tor-circuit-established-check timed out. Normally it should either fail quickly or show the result quickly. I don’t why /usr/bin/tor-circuit-established-check would timeout unless host and/or VM is under heavy load.

Note: Non-Compromise Indicators

That part of the log output will be improved in a future version.

Read full topic
